This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with face restoration from low resolution and noise, which is an important application of computer vision. The use of ensemble learning and sequential gating units also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The mention of benchmark datasets and image restoration models suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the use of adversarial training scheme suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
